    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Advertising Council Chooses Officers</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Stuart Elliott</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Elliott, Stuart</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Advertising Council of New York names John H Costello chairman, succeeding James G Oates; Costello has been vice chairman of council since 1997; Andrea Alstrup will serve as vice chairwoman (Advertising column) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Advertising Council in New York, which coordinates public service campaigns for Madison Avenue, has named John H. Costello, chief executive at MVP.com in Chicago, as chairman. He succeeds James G. Oates, the former president at the Leo Burnett Company in Chicago, part of the B Com3 Group.</p>
        <p>Mr. Costello, who will serve as chairman for a year, had been a vice chairman of the council since 1997.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Advertising Council in New York, which coordinates public service campaigns for Madison Avenue, has named John H. Costello, chief executive at MVP.com in Chicago, as chairman. He succeeds James G. Oates, the former president at the Leo Burnett Company in Chicago, part of the B Com3 Group.</p>
        <p>Mr. Costello, who will serve as chairman for a year, had been a vice chairman of the council since 1997.</p>
        <p>Andrea J. Alstrup, vice president for advertising and marketing at Johnson &amp; Johnson in New Brunswick, N.J., will serve as the vice chairwoman for the next year, representing corporate members of the council.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
